desc:
Category Aluminum Tanker Trailers 
 The three-axle diesel semi-trailer transporter will be exported in batches to the Nigerian National Petroleum 
 Corporation in Africa. The vehicle's overall dimensions (mm): 12200*2500*3850. The walking part of the semi-trailer is equipped with: 90# traction pin, 3-axle 13-ton Fuhua axle, 12R22.5 tire, 500L tool box, with ABS, two spare tire racks, reinforced mechanical suspension, single-acting outrigger, 8*16*100mm spring. Tank part: The tank volume is about 45m3 cubic meters, divided into three compartments, straight tank, the tank body is made of Q355B material, three European standard tank ports, three seabed valves, three bottom oil loading, with oil product display, independent ladder welded on the front of the tank body, movable European ladder with anti-skid plate, with aluminum alloy folding guardrail, anti-skid walkway installed in the middle of the top of the tank body, the front end of the barrel is fully welded with a drip hole connected to a small ball valve, and two 8 kg carbon steel fire extinguisher cylinders 
 Delivery time: 15-25 days 
 Tank volume: 40000L-45000L 
 Application: Trailers can be used to transport various fuels such as gasoline, diesel, kerosene, etc.

desc: Dump trucks are highly efficient engineering transport vehicles widely used in scenarios such as mining and construction. Equipped with a unique hydraulic lifting system, they can tilt the cargo box via controlled cylinders to automatically unload bulk materials like sand, gravel, and earth quickly. This significantly improves loading and unloading efficiency while reducing labor costs.
